constructor.notice: Create a new ballot to choose one of `proposalNames`.

delegate(address).notice: Delegate your vote to the voter `to`.

giveRightToVote(address).notice: Give `voter` the right to vote on this ballot. May only be called by `chairperson`.

giveRightToVoteBatch(address[]).notice: Batch version: give multiple voters the right to vote in a single tx. Addresses that already have rights or have voted are skipped.

isTie().notice: Convenience: returns true if there is a tie between 2+ proposals.

vote(uint256).notice: Give your vote (including votes delegated to you) to proposal `proposal`.

winnerName().notice: Returns the name of the single winner (kept for compatibility).

winningProposal().notice: Original behavior: returns a single winning proposal index (the first one with the highest voteCount).

winningProposals().notice: New: returns all proposal indices that share the highest vote count.
